HEADWORD: Commutable
<hw>Com*mut"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>commutabilis</ets>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being commuted or
interchanged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The predicate and subject are not <qex>commutable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Whately.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commutableness</ent>⟦br⟧
